Copyright.AdditionalInfo: Lithoprobe THOT Transect MT - Trans-Hudson Orogen Transect Broad band magnetotelluric data collected during Lithoprobe project. Date published September 1, 1994 Series Geological Survey of Canada, Seismic and Magnetotelluric Data 171 Issue Lithoprobe THOT Transect MT Author Brian Roberts Contact Information Government of Canada; Natural Resources Canada; Earth Sciences Sector; Canada Centre for Mapping and Earth Observation Contact: Telephone: 1-819-564-4857 Telephone: 1-800-661-2638 (Toll Free in Canada and USA.) E-mail: NRCan.geogratis-geogratis.RNCan@canada.ca Purpose: The data archive is a planned output of the LITHOPROBE project and is meant to be accessible to all Canadians. Regional seismic lines and magnetotelluric sites provide an excellent framework for understanding crustal scale geological features in many important areas of the Country. Licence Open Government Licence - Canada (http://open.canada.ca/en/open-government-licence-canada) These data were converted from the original EDI SPECTRA format using EMTF FCU 4.0 developed by Anna Kelbert, USGS last updated in Nov 2017. This novel algorithm allows for estimation of full error covariances from cross-power spectra. We thank Xavier Garcia and Gary Egbert for valuable advice that helped develop the spectra conversion algorithm.
